<item>
            <title>[LU-5099] Transfer the object&apos;s type via dio_insert() API to allow OSD set remote object type correctly</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5099</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When the LFSCK found a dangling name entry, it may be required to re-create the lost remote MDT-object. The LFSCK needs to know the file&apos;s type for the re-creating.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Generally, the LFSCK can get the file&apos;s type from the name entry. Unfortunately, when we insert the name entry to the directory via dt_insert(), the sponsor does not transfer the file&apos;s type. It is not a problem for local case, because the OSD can get the file&apos;s type internally via checking the MDT-object directly. But for remote case, when the OSD handle the local insert, it cannot know the remote object&apos;s type. In DNE phase I, we only support remote directory, so the OSD can assume that the file&apos;s type is S_IFDIR. But such assumption will be wrong when enable remote object for normal file.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
